Supplementary Materials Statement

The following supplementary data files are included:

1) Supplementary_Data_01_harmonized_phenotype_data.csv
   Harmonized observation-level phenotype dataset used for all main analyses.

2) Supplementary_Data_02_study_metadata.csv
   Study-level metadata and source annotations.

3) Supplementary_Data_03_observation_summary.csv
   Mutation-level summary statistics from the harmonized dataset.

4) Supplementary_Data_04_model_comparison.csv
   Model comparison metrics (M0--M3) used in Figure 2 and Results.

5) Supplementary_Data_05_epistasis_matrix.csv
   Observed, expected, and residual epistasis values used in Figure 3 analyses.

6) Supplementary_Data_06_mutation_classifications.csv
   Evidence-tier mutation classifications used for framework and prioritization panels.
